not store the index column so that when you load your.csv again,

13
00:00:37,350 --> 00:00:40,375
you don't get an unnecessary duplicated index column.

14
00:00:40,375 --> 00:00:43,475
There's also a number of other arguments that you can specify,

15
00:00:43,475 --> 00:00:47,810
such as the encoding in order to ensure your data is stored in the right format.

16
00:00:47,810 --> 00:00:50,195
You can also write data to a database.

17
00:00:50,195 --> 00:00:54,485
For example, with sql light through Pandas to sql function with sql alchemy.

18
00:00:54,485 --> 00:00:57,320
Here, foe example we can specify the table name,

19
00:00:57,320 --> 00:00:59,660
our sql alchemy engine connection,

20
00:00:59,660 --> 00:01:02,900
and additional arguments such as if_exists='append',

21
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:05,210
where here we insert new values to

22
