an existing table if the table we're trying to create already exists.

23
00:01:08,910 --> 00:01:14,225
Another argument is index label to specify the column or columns to use as the index,

24
00:01:14,225 --> 00:01:16,665
which in this case we want to use ID.

25
00:01:16,665 --> 00:01:21,460
It's critical to also maintain different instances where versions of the data.

26
00:01:21,460 --> 00:01:22,880
At the very minimum,

27
00:01:22,880 --> 00:01:24,905
you should have two versions of your data.

28
00:01:24,905 --> 00:01:28,580
One version should be your raw data stored directly after the gathering stage,

29
00:01:28,580 --> 00:01:30,515
and one should be your clean data.

30
